Peiker Acustic GmbH & Co. KG (styled all-lower-case as "peiker acustic" in the official company logo) is a family-owned and -operated company, based in Friedrichsdorf, Taunus, Germany, with about 825 employees  worldwide. Since 1946, the company has specialized in manufacturing electronic products including microphones, loudspeakers, handsets for radio and mobile telephone use, Bluetooth hands-free kits, and in-vehicle multimedia systems.
In 2013, the Peiker group of companies generated approximately 173 million  euros in sales. After the closure of large portions of the Milupa plant in Friedrichsdorf, Peiker is now the city's largest employer.
